.TH "__ice_set_coalesce" 9 "__ice_set_coalesce" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
__ice_set_coalesce \- set ITR/INTRL values for the device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" __ice_set_coalesce
.BI "(struct net_device *netdev "  ","
.BI "struct ethtool_coalesce *ec "  ","
.BI "int q_num "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "netdev" 12
pointer to the netdev associated with this query
.IP "ec" 12
ethtool structure to fill with driver's coalesce settings
.IP "q_num" 12
queue number to get the coalesce settings for
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If the caller passes in a negative q_num then we set the coalesce settings
for all Tx/Rx queues, else use the actual q_num passed in.
